From: Alexander Duyck <alexander.h.duyck@redhat.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Dec 2014 19:41:17 -0800
Subject: [PATCH 68/91] ethernet/broadcom: Use napi_alloc_skb instead of
 netdev_alloc_skb_ip_align
Patch-mainline: v3.19-rc1
Git-commit: 45abfb1069e4c365f6c1e2fc97c5927272725bfa (partial)
References: bsc#922056 FATE#318604

This patch replaces the calls to netdev_alloc_skb_ip_align in the
copybreak paths.

Cc: Gary Zambrano <zambrano@broadcom.com>
Cc: Florian Fainelli <f.fainelli@gmail.com>
Cc: Ariel Elior <ariel.elior@qlogic.com>
Signed-off-by: Alexander Duyck <alexander.h.duyck@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Cho, Yu-Chen <acho@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/bnx2x/bnx2x_cmn.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/bnx2x/bnx2x_cmn.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/bnx2x/bnx2x_cmn.c
@@ -1015,7 +1015,7 @@ static int bnx2x_rx_int(struct bnx2x_fas
 		 */
 		if ((bp->dev->mtu > ETH_MAX_PACKET_SIZE) &&
 		    (len <= RX_COPY_THRESH)) {
-			skb = netdev_alloc_skb_ip_align(bp->dev, len);
+			skb = napi_alloc_skb(&fp->napi, len);
 			if (skb == NULL) {
 				DP(NETIF_MSG_RX_ERR | NETIF_MSG_RX_STATUS,
 				   "ERROR  packet dropped because of alloc failure\n");
